paces: L*a*b* and L*u*v*.  Depending onjust how perceptually linear these color spaces are, this seems like areasonable approach.  I've been meaning to try this but haven't foundthe time ...Perceptually equidistant colormaps should work fine for 2D imageanalysis applications.  Has anyone even considered attempting to dothe same thing for 3D stuff given that your colors are wildlytransformed by the illumination model?  The one saving grace is thatthe human perceptual system is pretty good at judging an object'scolor even under varying illumination conditions.-Tom"At 8,500 feet you rarely see a tax attorney or an obvious hairpiece."							- ZippyThomas C. Palmer		North Carolina Supercomputing CenterCray Research, Inc.		Phone: (919) 248-1117PO Box 12889			Arpanet: palmer@ncsc.org3021 Cornwallis RoadResearch Triangle Park, NC27709From disuns2!sicsun!chx400!chx400!cernvax!mcsun!uunet!ukma!rex!samsung!usc!zaphod.mps.ohio-state.edu!mips!apple!motcsd!dms!rotberg Fri Apr 19 13:05:10 MET DST 1991Article: 4081 of comp.graphicsPath: disuns2!sicsun!chx400!chx400!cernvax!mcsun!uunet!ukma!rex!samsung!usc!zaphod.mps.ohio-state.edu!mips!apple!motcsd!dms!rotbergFrom: rotberg@dms.UUCP (Ed Rotberg)Newsgroups: comp.graphicsSubject: Re; RGB to CYMK?? Anybody know of an algorithm?? (SUMMARY - LONG!!!)Keywords: RGB CMYK color conversion HSV HSLMessage-ID: <1224@dms.UUCP>Date: 18 Mar 91 18:19:51 GMTOrganization: Atari Games Inc., Milpitas, CALines: 670Thanks to all who responded,  I am posting this summary of replies that Ireceived to my inquiry about RGB to CMYK conversion.Message #1 (47 lines)>From weitek!pyramid!ratmandu.csd.sgi.com!shreiner Thu Mar 14 05:42:59 1991Received: from pyramid.UUCP by weitek.COM (4.1/SMI-4.1)	id AA22462; Wed, 13 Mar 91 21:31:04 PSTReceived: by pyramid.pyramid.com (5.61/OSx5.0-890710)	id AA09730; Wed, 13 Mar 91 21:16:41 -0800Received: from relay.sgi.com by SGI.COM via SMTP (5.65+bind 1.5+ida/910110.SGI)	for pyram